title: UGA, Athens-Clarke County Government Reopen; CCSD Closed Monday - Flagpole
meta_description: Athens received about three inches of snow on Saturday, but the UGA campus and local government services like transit have reopened as it quickly began to melt on Sunday afternoon, although some roads could remain treacherous. The University of Georgia reopened this afternoon, and classes will proceed as usual on Monday. The Clarke County School District, though, announced there will be no school Monday. "This decision was made with great care after CCSD staff diligently drove throughout the entire county this afternoon and encountered areas of ice and standing water that will refreeze overnight to create unsafe conditions for our buses, young drivers and staff," the district said in a news release.
